 791:     """Fast, re-entrant locking.


 792: 


 793:     Under uncongested conditions, the lock is never acquired but only


 794:     counted.  Only when a second thread comes in and notices that the


 795:     lock is needed, it acquires the lock and notifies the first thread


 796:     to release it when it's done.  This is all made possible by the


 797:     wonderful GIL.


 798:     """
